BEGIN_PGML
Fill in the blanks with the numbers [$little] and [$big] (using each number only once) to create an equation where [`x`] has the greatest possible value.
a.  [_]{$little}{3} [`{}+x={}`] [_]{$big}{3}

a.  [_]{$big}{3} [`{}={}`] [_]{$little}{3}[`{}\cdot x`]

END_PGML

############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
a.  Consider which is greater: [`[$big] - [$little]`] or [`[$little] - [$big]\text{?}`] To make the largest value for [`x\text{,}`] you must put [$little] in the left blank and [$big] in the right blank because you solve this equation by subtracting [$little] from both sides. This makes [`x = [$big] - [$little]\text{,}`] which is the largest possible value for [`x\text{.}`]

a.  Consider which is larger: [`\frac{[$big]}{[$little]}`] or [`\frac{[$little]}{[$big]}\text{?}`] To make the largest value for [`x\text{,}`] you must put [$big] in the left blank and [$little] in the right blank because you solve this equation by dividing both sides by [$little]. This makes [`x = \frac{[$big]}{[$little]}\text{,}`] which is the largest possible value for [`x\text{.}`]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

